        <title>Some Brief Thoughts on Trump and Russia (with links)</title>
        
        <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://micro.oxus.net/uploads/2018/99c30dc6f5.jpg&quot; width=&quot;600&quot; height=&quot;427&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It seems to me that Trump‚Äôs love of Russian is &lt;a href=&quot;https://foreignpolicy.com/2018/07/19/the-manchurian-idiot-helsinki-putin-trump/&quot;&gt;not about policy&lt;/a&gt;, but about a &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/HeerJeet/status/1019003028265885696&quot;&gt;shared racist, patriarchal, world view&lt;/a&gt;. That, and his &lt;a href=&quot;https://newrepublic.com/article/143586/trumps-russian-laundromat-trump-tower-luxury-high-rises-dirty-money-international-crime-syndicate&quot;&gt;financial dependency&lt;/a&gt; on the Russian mob. I think that those things, along with &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.politico.com/magazine/story/2018/07/20/confession-of-a-no-longer-russiagate-skeptic-219022&quot;&gt;Russian meddling in the election&lt;/a&gt;, are enough to explain Trump‚Äôs actions, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.vox.com/conversations/2017/2/22/14697718/trump-putin-helsinki-meeting-hillary-clinton&quot;&gt;without need to invoke the ‚Äòpee tapes‚Äô&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What to do about Russian meddling? I agree with Seth Ackerman that rather than freaking out about ‚Äútreason,‚Äù we should be looking at ‚Äú&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.jacobinmag.com/2018/07/russia-election-meddling-putin&quot;&gt;practical steps to deal with the problem&lt;/a&gt;‚Äù which &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.jacobinmag.com/2018/07/trump-putin-russia-liberals-helsinki&quot;&gt;few people are doing&lt;/a&gt;‚Ä¶ I suppose some think yelling ‚Äútreason‚Äù enough will win Republicans over to impeaching Trump, but it seems &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/aponline/2018/07/19/us/politics/ap-us-trump-democrats-treason.html&quot;&gt;hard to tell&lt;/a&gt; if that would work or just backfire? Personally, I would really like to see the US &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.vox.com/2018/4/3/17189906/russian-election-hacking-paper-ballots&quot;&gt;switch to paper ballots&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As far as the well documented history of the US interfering in foreign elections is concerned, I think Nathan Robinson is right that ‚Äú&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.currentaffairs.org/2018/07/liberalism-and-empire&quot;&gt;Trump exceptionalism will kill every one of your brain cells&lt;/a&gt;.‚Äù And commentators should retain some perspective, but those on the left should equally be wary of descending into the kind of ‚Äú&lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/whataboutery&quot;&gt;whataboutery&lt;/a&gt;‚Äù that liberals so often use to undermine those issues the left holds dear.&lt;/p&gt;

